snd-hda-codec-cs8409-imac (1.19) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Mute internal speakers in the driver via the amp-enable GPIO, not via the
    generic auto-mute. Testing showed the headphone path and speakers both work,
    but the speakers parse as line-outs (speaker_outs=0) so "Auto-Mute Mode"
    defaults off, and WirePlumber turns it off anyway and does only cosmetic
    port switching — so the speakers never muted on headphone insert. Now the
    tip-sense poll drives GPIO4 (the external TAS5764 amp enable) directly:
    amps on when nothing is plugged, off when a headphone is inserted. This is
    conflict-free (neither the parser nor userspace touch that GPIO) and gives
    guaranteed silence. suppress_auto_mute is restored so the confusing,
    userspace-disabled "Auto-Mute Mode" control is gone. Applied from the poll,
    the unsol handler, and at init/build.

 -- Peter Shev <peter@shev.it>  Wed, 25 Jun 2026 16:30:00 +0000

snd-hda-codec-cs8409-imac (1.18) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Fix tip-sense polarity. The 1.16 boot read (DET_STATUS1=0x16, bit7=0) was
    taken with the jack UNPLUGGED, not plugged as first assumed, so a plug
    present reads bit7=1: set CS42L83_TIP_SENSE_LEVEL_PRESENT=1. (This is also
    the fail-safe direction — if still wrong, speakers just don't mute rather
    than going silent at idle.)

 -- Peter Shev <peter@shev.it>  Wed, 25 Jun 2026 15:00:00 +0000

snd-hda-codec-cs8409-imac (1.17) resolute; urgency=medium

  * HP/speaker auto-mute via polling. Diagnostics (1.16) confirmed the CS42L83
    delivers NO jack unsolicited response through the CS8409 on the iMac, and
    that the shared CS42L42 TSRS_PLUG_STATUS encoding does not apply (it reads
    single bits, never the 0/3 plug/unplug values). So: drive detection from a
    500ms tip-sense poll (new cs8409_cs42l83_jack_poll_work) and read the raw
    tip-sense LEVEL from DET_STATUS1 (0x1b77) bit7 instead. Measured plugged =
    0x16 (bit7=0), so present == tip-sense-clear (CS42L83_TIP_SENSE_LEVEL_PRESENT
    = 0; flip to 1 if backwards). Poll is started in hw_init, re-armed on
    resume, cancelled on suspend/remove. Logs the registers only on change.

 -- Peter Shev <peter@shev.it>  Wed, 25 Jun 2026 14:00:00 +0000

snd-hda-codec-cs8409-imac (1.16) resolute; urgency=medium

  * DIAGNOSTIC build (not a finished feature). Logs every CS42L83 unsolicited
    response (raw res, before filtering) and dumps both candidate tip-sense
    sources (TSRS_PLUG_STATUS 0x130f and DET_STATUS1 0x1b77) on every jack
    read, all at info level. Used to determine whether plug/unplug generate
    interrupts at all and what the inverted tip-sense actually reads, so the
    1.15 auto-mute detection can be finalized.

