snd-hda-codec-cs8409-imac (1.15) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Headphone/speaker auto-mute: replace the phantom always-present headphone
    jack with real tip-sense detection so the internal speakers and the
    headphone become mutually exclusive (HP in -> speakers mute & HP plays;
    HP out -> speakers play). Reads the inverted CS42L83 tip-sense in a new
    cs8409_cs42l83_jack_detect() and lets the generic parser's auto-mute
    handle the switching (dropped suppress_auto_mute and the forced
    hp_jack_in=1 / NO_PRESENCE pincfg). The internal speakers stay a fixed
    always-present sink, so userspace keeps a real output in both states (no
    PipeWire "Dummy Output" regression). Jack polarity is isolated to the
    CS42L83_JACK_PRESENT_ON_TS_PLUG macro; detection logs to dmesg.

